name: Rambut Siwi Temple
address: Yeh Embang Kangin, Mendoyo, Jembrana Regency, Bali 82261, Indonesia
review 1: Beautiful temple by the sea, when we visited we were the only tourists. Felt incredibly magic with a view over the setting sun and local kids playing football on the beach. Opt-in for the tour, our guide was amazing, sweet and knowledgable!

review 4: Beautiful tranquil piece of land in the beach.
review 5:
A magnificent Hindu temple that was built in the 16th-century overlooking the black sand beaches of the west Bali and green rice paddies around the temple itself.

The temple is easily can be found which is off the main street from Denpasar to Gilimanuk the port to get the ferry crossing over to Java.

Entrance ticket to the temple is only IDR 20,000/person. You should wear a sarong to enter the temple which are available at the ticket counter but it is convenient to bring your own.

From the main temple, you should walk to visit the Penataran temple and Goa Dasar Agung ( a sacred cave) which are down by the beach and during the low tide you can have such a lovely walk along the black sand beach. If the weather is good, it is fantastic to visit the temple around sunset.

review 2: Been known this restaurant by last year, one of my favourite restaurant during trip in Bali. Very authentic, so I prefer go with the Chicken Nyatnyat. The place looks good for evening, surrounded by rice fields so relaxing. Repeat order? Yes pleaseüëçüèª
review 3: Absolutely incredible restaurant, even with a small menu. Seems like quality over quantity, definitely recommend the fried chicken. And in the back a breathtaking view with calming music
review 4: Most loved is the Mujair Goreng. Most importantly, the service is very good. We love the ambience, too, it has a beautiful lawn for relaxing overlooking paddy fields. You need a jacket as the wind can be strong. The place is clean and the d√©cor is of Pinterest's style. Nice. It's a very good option when you want a rest on Gilimanuk-Denpasar route because the cleanliness of nearby eateries is not for the weak stomach. As for the price, it is very good, also in comparison with the next-door restaurant which has no price in its menu and it can be shocking when we go to the counter to pay. Not this place. It is honest and has ample parking, too. Very recommended. Thumbs up. We've been waiting for this to come for a long time.
review 5: The food here is incredible, I loved the chicken especially.
